RACE.RACE_TEXT: My Lady's Manor Timber S. MONKTON RACE 1 3M Timber CR: N/A. Stakes Purse 50000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. To be ridden by amateur riders acceptable to the race committee. Five-year-olds, 160 lbs.; older, 165 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOMGARROW (IRE) stalked patiently in second, ridden to the lead after 14th fence, led last two fences and drew off after last under a vigorous hand ride. VINTAGE VINNIE (IRE) led for two miles, was overtaken after the 14th fence, outrun in stretch yet stayed on for second. MYSTIC STRIKE was unhurried from the start, traveled in the rear, gained some as pace slowed last half mile, got up for third in the stretch. GOODOLDTIMES (IRE) raced up with the pack early, tired and unable to keep up the final half mile, losing third in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Goodoldtimes (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: up with pack early, unable to keep up final mile

ENTRY.NAME: Mystic Strike
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, traveled in rear, up for third in stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Vintage Vinnie (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: led for two miles, overtaken after 14, stayed on for second

ENTRY.NAME: Tomgarrow (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked in second, ridden to lead after 14, drew off after last

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MONKTON RACE 2 3M Timber CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON OVER TIMBER. To be ridden by amateur riders acceptable to the race committee. Five-year-olds, 160 lbs.; older, 165 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FASHION LINE led for 14 fences, was headed two fences out and dueled to the wire to prevail. TO BE OR NOT TO BE tracked the leader, roused and dueled from last two fences a head in front, then nipped at the wire. BROOKLYN SPEIGHTS traveled in rear, was no threat, got round and eased in stretch. CAUSE FOR PARDON clipped the 10th fence and pitched rider off.

ENTRY.NAME: Brooklyn Speights
ENTRY.COMMENT: traveled in rear, no threat, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Fashion Line
ENTRY.COMMENT: led for 14 fences, headed last two, prevailed all out in stretch

ENTRY.NAME: To Be Or Not to Be
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leader, roused and dueled from last two fences to wire

ENTRY.NAME: Cause for Pardon
ENTRY.COMMENT: clipped fence 10 and pitched rider off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MONKTON RACE 3 3M Timber CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON OVER TIMBER. To be ridden by amateur riders acceptable to the race committee. Five-year-olds, 160 lbs.; older, 165 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STOLEN SHOES (GB) led from the start, vied for lead mid race with MR. FINE THREADS, drew clear of that foe before last fence and increased margin in the stretch under a vigorous hand ride. MR. FINE THREADS vied with foe for the lead mid race, held narrow lead three fences out, then overtaken before final fence and stayed well for second. ADJUTANT (GB) lost touch with the field, refused at fence 14 unseating the rider. QUALITY CHOICE dropped back after ten fences and was pulled up. FAMILY TREE (GB) fell at the 8th fence.

ENTRY.NAME: Mr. Fine Threads
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied with foe for lead mid race, narrow lead three out, overtaken

ENTRY.NAME: Adjutant (GB)
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost touch with field, refused at fence 14 unseating rider

ENTRY.NAME: Quality Choice
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back after ten fences and pulled up

ENTRY.NAME: Stolen Shoes (GB)
ENTRY.COMMENT: led from start, vied for lead mid race, drew clear before last

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MONKTON RACE 4 3M Timber CR: N/A. Allowance Purse 15000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A TIMBER OR HURDLE STAKES IN 2022-2023. To be ridden by apprentice riders. 170 lbs. Non-winners of two races over timber, allowed 5 lbs.; of a race, 10 lbs. Riders who have never won a race, allowed 5 lbs. No other rider allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MASTER SEVILLE rated mid pack, held third position at last fence, then closed strong in the stretch drive to get up for the win. AWESOME ADRIAN took the lead at the 8th fence, led over the last fence, then was outfinished in the stretch. ROYAL RUSE traveled in the rear, made a mild gain from the second from last fence to the wire. MERCOEUR (FR) stalked the pacesetter, weakened the last quarter mile though stayed on. POCKET TALK (IRE) dropped back and was distanced mid race, got round.

ENTRY.NAME: Pocket Talk (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back and distanced mid race, got round

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Adrian
ENTRY.COMMENT: took lead at 8th fence, led over last fence, outfinished stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Mercoeur (FR)
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pacesetter, weakened last quarter mile, stayed on

ENTRY.NAME: Royal Ruse
ENTRY.COMMENT: traveled in rear, mild gain from second last to wire

ENTRY.NAME: Master Seville
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated mid pack, closed strong in stretch drive to get up for win
